'''Spongiosum''' is the Latin adjective for "spongy".  The term is used in [[anatomy]] for tissues that become filled with blood:  ''[[corpus spongiosum]]'', ''stratum spongiosum'' of the [[decidua]].  It is also used in [[binomial nomenclature]] of organisms, such as the seaweed ''[[Codium]] spongiosum''.

